2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the queuing system in the context of multimedia communication and stream computing, which are relevant to this sub-category. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the reliability of queueing systems, which is a key concern in control systems. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper mentions multimedia communication as one of the contexts in which the queuing system is applicable. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the distributions of arrival and service processes that maximize and minimize the capacity of the system, which is relevant to this sub-category.
